reviewText: Great Film, exactly what I was expecting when I purchased it as I saw it in a Museum. Truly the best of William Wegman!

waste of money...too weird and not enough of his later dog posing videos - very disapointed with this purchase and ended up tossing the DVDs in the trash and didn't give to someone or save - worthless
Ok, ok, not the most artful of clips, but Pure Wegman, nonetheless. You can't love him, without loving his dogs!

If you only know Wegman's calendar-friendly commercial work--check out his roots.  Wegman wass unabashedly and outrageously one of the finest artists working in the seventies.  As raw as direct as anything Bruce Nauman had done, and as clever, intimate and tongue-in-cheek as John Baldesarri at his finest.

Wegman is brilliant and this collection is tribute to an artist at the top of heap of the conceptual posse!
